"Although we do not undertake an exhaustive historical analysis today of the full scope of the Second Amendment , nothing in our opinion should be taken to cast doubt on longstanding prohibitions on the possession of firearms by felons and the mentally ill, or laws forbidding the carrying of firearms in sensitive places such as schools and government buildings, or laws imposing conditions and qualifications on the commercial sale of arms."-US Supreme Court in D.C. v. HellerSo the US Supreme court recognizes that some restrictions are reasonable such as not allowing felons to own guns or prohibiting people from carrying guns in school areas.